---
title: One-Pan Smoky Pork Tacos with Green Pepper, Pickled Onion & Monterey Jack Cheese
description: These ground pork tacos taste slow-cooked, thanks to Southwest-style seasonings plus tomato paste for umami-packed richness, and savory onion and green pepper. It’s all stuffed into steamy tortillas with Monterey Jack cheese, pickled onion, tomato, and chipotle crema—basically, everything we crave on taco night and then some.

image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/66ba4be6fb4859096c8b62a5-154816ee.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/66ba4be6fb4859096c8b62a5-en-US.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/one-pan-smoky-pork-tacos-66ba4be6fb4859096c8b62a5
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
cuisine: Mexican
time required: 35 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 860 kcal
  fat: 50 g
  saturated fat: 17 g
  carbohydrates: 63 g
  sugar: 17 g
  protein: 34 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1400 mg
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry produce.

Halve and peel @onion{1}(peeled and halved); thinly slice one half and finely chop remaining.

Core, deseed, and dice @long green pepper{1}(cored, deseeded, and diced into 1/2-inch pieces).

Dice @tomato{1}(diced).

Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%oz}(roughly chopped).

In a #medium bowl{}, combine sliced onion, @white wine vinegar{5%tsp}, @water{1%tbsp}, @sugar{2%tsp}, and @salt{1/2%tsp}. Stir until sugar and salt have mostly dissolved. Set aside to pickle, stirring occasionally, until ready to serve.

> We used 1/2 tsp of salt for pickling.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @ground pork{10%oz} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Transfer to a #plate{} and set aside.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add green pepper and chopped onion; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Return pork to pan along with @southwest spice blend{1%tbsp}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, half the @tomato paste{1}, and @water{1/4%cup}. Cook, scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pan, until mixture is thickened and saucy, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

While filling cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{1.5%tbsp}, a bit of onion pickling liquid to taste (start with 1/4 tsp and add more if desired), and a pinch of @chipotle powder{1%tsp}. Stir in @water{} 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> Add more chipotle powder to taste if you like things spicy.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates; fill with pork filling, @monterey jack cheese{1/4%cup}, tomato, cilantro, pickled onion (draining first), and crema. 

> TIP: Alternatively, put everything in individual serving bowls and let everyone assemble their own tacos!

> Ground Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160º.